<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7416a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-12">February 12,
                                1942</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. Please deliver the following personal message from the President to
                            His Excellency Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“I have this moment signed the bill appropriating five hundred
                                    million dollars to render financial aid to China<note n="85" xml:id="d350fn85">56 Stat. 89.</note> and it is now law.
                                    Franklin D. Roosevelt.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>